<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="273" pageId="1" pageNumber="272" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1499,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1499,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium-sized leafhoppers. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[693,825,1499,1526]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 35, 39</figureCitation>
) with median longitudinal carina complete extending from the anterior to posterior margin. Pronotum and base of clavus (
<figureCitation box="[930,1061,1535,1562]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 35, 36</figureCitation>
) punctate. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1311,1385,1535,1562]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1399,1428,1535,1562]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">16</figureCitation>
) costal margin with supranumerary R branches along apical half. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[1061,1133,1571,1598]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1145,1174,1572,1598]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">18</figureCitation>
) narrow and elongated. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[275,346,1607,1634]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[358,387,1608,1634]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">22</figureCitation>
) with elongate dorsally curved pair of atrial processes; shaft with apical portion expanded with pair of lateral processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1499,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1679,1706]" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Coloration.</emphasis>
Dull yellow (
<figureCitation box="[491,620,1679,1706]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 11–13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[632,703,1680,1706]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">33–40</figureCitation>
) with dark maculae on crown that may extend to pronotum (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 35, 39</figureCitation>
). Forewing milky hyaline; male with smoky median longitudinal band extending from the clavus to apical cells, absent in female (
<figureCitation box="[415,488,1751,1778]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[500,529,1752,1778]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[540,571,1751,1778]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1499,2030]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,152,863]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="273" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,1788,1814]" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">External morphology.</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[541,670,1787,1814]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 35, 39</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, distinctly narrower than pronotum. Crown (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Fig. 35, 39</figureCitation>
) moderately produced anteriorly, expanded laterad anterad of eyes; coronal suture carinate and elevated towards apex; surface depressed between coronal suture and lateral margins of crown, texture with numerous longitudinal and oblique striations; anterior margin rounded or angled with distinct carina at crown-face transition; lateral margins, adjacent to eyes, raised and carinated. Frons, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[958,1091,1931,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 36, 40</figureCitation>
), oblique and slightly convex; inflated; with median longitudinal carina dorsally. Antenna moderately long; flagellum approximately one-fourth length of body. Antennal ledge carinate, in frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[791,862,2003,2030]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[877,907,2004,2030]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[919,948,2003,2030]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">15</figureCitation>
) narrow, flap-like; in lateral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="273" pageId="1" pageNumber="272">Figs 36, 40</figureCitation>
) slightly oblique. Gena broadly rounded, not emarginated below eye (
<figureCitation box="[978,1050,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1065,1095,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1108,1139,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">15</figureCitation>
). Clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[1268,1340,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1356,1386,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1399,1428,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">15</figureCitation>
) rectangular; with parallel lateral margins; ventral margin straight or slightly arched.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[324,450,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 35, 39</figureCitation>
) punctate; lateral margins carinate and strongly convergent anteriorly. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1359,1431,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,180,261,288]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">16</figureCitation>
) hyaline; venation distinct; costal margin with supranumerary R branches along apical half; s crossvein slightly anterior to r-m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[319,327,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">2</subScript>
; r-m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[384,392,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">1</subScript>
absent; three or more m-cu crossveins present; three anteapical cells (median one open or closed) and four apical cells; inner apical cell narrow and elongate; clavus with base punctate; appendix narrow, extending to second apical cell. Hind wing with veins R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[741,767,386,400]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">4+5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[843,868,386,400]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">1+2</subScript>
separated by short crossvein; crossvein m-cu short. Hind femur with macrosetal formula 2+1+1; tibia with AD row with two or three intercalary microsetae between macrosetae; tibia with AV row with 5–6 macrosetae restricted to distal half; first tarsomere with two parallel rows of small setae on plantar surface; apex with three platellae; second tarsomere apex with two apical platellae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,402,512,539]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Male pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[587,663,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[680,709,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">17</figureCitation>
) slightly angulate posterodorsally; without lobes or processes; macrosetae restricted to apical area. Valve subrectangular; with sclerotized median line. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1431,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 3–4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,222,585,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">17–18</figureCitation>
) narrow; ventral surface with scattered fine setae. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[929,1001,584,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1013,1042,585,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">19</figureCitation>
) T-shaped. Style (
<figureCitation box="[1244,1345,584,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 5–6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1357,1428,585,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">19–20</figureCitation>
) with apodeme long; apophysis short and stout; apex hooked on inner side and with distinct long spine on outer side. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[276,377,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 7–8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[389,460,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">21–22</figureCitation>
) with pair of long dorsally curved atrial processes; shaft depressed dorsoventrally, with pair of preapical lateral processes; gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,425,728,755]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Female terminalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[579,646,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) wider than long; posterolateral angles reduced. First valvula (
<figureCitation box="[1347,1428,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) sculpturing pattern with dorsal area strigate and ventroapical area maculose. Second valvulae (
<bibRefCitation author="Hill, B. G." box="[1223,1342,765,791]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" pagination="78 - 79" refId="ref5589" refString="Hill, B. G. (1973) A new genus of Cicadellidae from Brazil. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 75 (1), 78 - 79." type="journal article" year="1973">Hill, 1973</bibRefCitation>
: Figs C, D) with irregular teeth crowded apically.
</paragraph>
